Requesterpool@jpdev.pro

Score1636
Tested byTestaro, procedure ts24
Scored byTestilo, procedure tsp24
Digested byTestilo, procedure tdp24

Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of accessibility Tests.

The battery includes 1353 automated accessibility tests drawn from ten different packages: Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE.

These tests were run on the web page named above and gave the page a score of 1636, where 0 would be perfect.

Issue summary

Special issues

log: Score 94. This is based on the amount of browser error logging and miscellaneous logging during the tests.

solos: Score 34. This is based on issues reported by unclassified tests. Details are in the report.

Classified issues

Issue focusIndication

WCAG: 2.4.7

Score: 356

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package testaro, test focInd, score 266 (Focused element displays no or a nostandard focus indicator)
  • Package alfa, test r65, score 106 (Element in the sequential focus order has no visible focus)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R62, score 114 (Element in the sequential focus order has no visible focus)

Issue textContrastAA

WCAG: 1.4.3

Score: 170

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r69, score 104 (Text outside widget has subminimum contrast)
  • Package axe, test color-contrast, score 59 (Element has insufficient color contrast)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AAA.1_4_6.G18.Fail, score 8 (Contrast between the text and its background is less than 4.5:1)
  • Package ibm, test IBMA_Color_Contrast_WCAG2AA, score 16 (Contrast ratio of text with background does not meet WCAG 2.1 AA)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R37, score 1 (Text has less than the minimum contrast)
  • Package wave, test c:contrast, score 75 (Very low contrast)

Issue overflowHidden

WCAG: 1.4.4

Score: 123

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r83, score 8 (Overflow is hidden or clipped if the text is enlarged)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R40, score 118 (Zoomed text node is clipped by a CSS overflow declaration)

Issue titleBad

WCAG: 1.3.1

Score: 94

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package testaro, test titledEl, score 92 (title attribute belongs to an inappropriate element)

Issue duplicateID

WCAG: 4.1.1

Score: 79

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r3, score 40 (Element id attribute value is not unique)
  • Package axe, test duplicate-id-active, score 6 (id attribute value of the active element is not unique)
  • Package axe, test duplicate-id, score 3 (id attribute value is not unique)
  • Package continuum, test 94, score 40 (Element contains an id attribute set to a value that is not unique in the DOM)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AAA.4_1_1.F77, score 20 (Duplicate id attribute value)
  • Package ibm, test RPT_Elem_UniqueId, score 24 (Element id attribute value is not unique within the document)
